We can go ahead with the following libs
- requests
- nltk
- flask
- pandas / numpy
- mayplotlib / seaborn

Discussed with @shvamabps :

## Challenge overview

- Challenge is run weekly. Each week there is one winner.
- Announced on Monday/Sunday night
- Challenge runs until a winner is declared. Then the next challenge is issued.
- Max of 5 steps in a challenge.
- Use time taken during attempts to break ties.

## Reference links

- Provide a REPL to people who attempt this challenge:
    - https://training.ilugc.in/
    - https://www.pythonanywhere.com/
    - https://repl.it/
@smitjethwa if you're online ping in the TG group. We're on a call right now for this.

# Regular Expression Questions

- Check whether a string starts and ends with a same character or not.
- Remove duplicate words from the sentence .
- Validate your email address .
- Extract the keywords of the text searched in an url.
- Determine whether the url is valid or not.
- Validate that the mobile number provided is correct or not based on the rules that number of digits that a particular mobile number should have. (Eg: In India the mobile number has 10 digits so write a regex for validating that number.)


Please check @theSage21  if I might need to make some changes in the questions.
